Text::Conjunct exports a single routine, 'conjunct', which joins a list of words or phrases together, separating the last two by the specified conjunction.

EXAMPLES

"conjunct 'or', 'apples', 'oranges'" gives 'apples or oranges'.

"conjunct 'or', 'apples', 'oranges', 'pears'" gives 'apples, oranges, or pears'.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

